The terminology is from Aristotle, <i>Eth. Nic.</i> III, 
1113.  What St Thomas here calls <i>voluntas</i>, and 
elsewhere <i>intentio</i> is the Aristotelian boulesis. Choice,
<i>electio</i>, is proairesis.  See my <i>Ethics and Natural Law</i>,
pp. 31 sq.; <i>Aquinas Ethicus</i> I, 52 - 54.
